Duplicate payment protection is fully implemented and enforced at both the application and persistence layers using idempotency handling.

In the original Loom walkthrough, I mistakenly forgot to demo the main critical feature regarding the Idempotency and the prevention of double charging. 
A short addendum video has been included to explicitly demonstrate this behaviour.

Idempotency Demo: see video Idempotency Demo.mp4

The addendum demonstrates:

Submitting an initial payment request
Re-submitting the same request (duplicate payload / idempotency key)
Prevention of a second charge
UI feedback indicating the duplicate request
Confirmation via payment history / audit trail

Reproduction Steps:

Submit a valid payment request
Re-submit the same request with the same idempotency key or payload
Observe:
No second charge is created
UI displays duplicate/error message
Audit trail reflects the correct state without duplication

This behaviour was prioritised as it is the most critical requirement in payment systems to ensure financial correctness and prevent double charging.
